# Spec Folder Management

## 📌 PURPOSE

Defines rules for managing spec folders in spec-kit.

Ensures one feature = one spec folder per branch.

---

## 🚨 CORE RULE

### 1 BRANCH = 1 SPEC FOLDER ONLY

---

## ⚙️ COMMAND RESPONSIBILITY

### /sp.specify

#### DO

* Create a new spec folder
* Check if spec already exists
* Warn before overwriting

#### DO NOT

* Do not silently overwrite existing spec

---

### /sp.clarify

#### DO

* Use existing spec folder
* Update existing `spec.md`

#### DO NOT

* Do not create new spec folder
* Do not generate new feature folder

---

## 🔍 SPEC DETECTION LOGIC

### DO

* Check for existing spec folder before execution

### EXAMPLE

```bash id="specdetect"
FEATURE_DIR=$(find specs/ -name "spec.md" -type f | head -1 | xargs dirname)

if [ -n "$FEATURE_DIR" ]; then
  echo "Existing spec folder found: $FEATURE_DIR"
fi
```

---

## ❗ VALIDATION RULE

### IF SPEC EXISTS

* `/sp.clarify` → MUST use existing spec
* `/sp.specify` → MUST warn user

---

### IF SPEC DOES NOT EXIST

* `/sp.clarify` → MUST FAIL

### ERROR MESSAGE

```id="specerror"
No spec folder found. Please run `/sp.specify` first.
```

---

## 🧾 FILE USAGE RULES

### DO

* `spec.md` → requirements
* `plan.md` → implementation plan
* `tasks.md` → actionable tasks

---

## 🔄 CORRECT WORKFLOW

```id="correctflow"
/sp.specify   → create spec folder  
/sp.clarify   → update spec.md  
/sp.plan      → update plan.md  
/sp.tasks     → update tasks.md  
```

---

## 🚫 INCORRECT WORKFLOW

```id="wrongflow"
/sp.specify   → create spec folder  
/sp.clarify   → ❌ must NOT create new folder  
```

---

## ⚠️ WHY THIS RULE EXISTS

### DO

* Maintain clear feature boundaries
* Avoid duplicate spec folders
* Keep workflow predictable

---

## 🚫 DO NOT RULES

* Do not create multiple spec folders in one branch
* Do not use `/sp.clarify` to create specs
* Do not bypass spec detection

---

## 🧠 AI ENFORCEMENT RULES

* MUST check for existing spec folder
* MUST use only one spec folder per branch
* MUST NOT create new spec in `/sp.clarify`
* MUST fail if spec missing for clarify
* MUST warn before overwrite in `/sp.specify`

---

